MacNUTT v. CITY OF NEW YORK et al. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. October, 1910.) Appeal from Special Term, New York County. Action by Margaret V. C. MacNutt against the City of New York and another. From a judgment of dismissal, plaintiff appeals. Reversed, and new trial ordered.

Argued before INGRAHAM, P. X, and McLAUGHLIN, LAUGHLIN, MILLER, and DOWLING, XT.

William Mason Smith, for appellant. Theodore Connoly, for respondents. INGRAHAM, P. J.

For the reasons stated in Ogden v. City of New York (decided herewith) 126 N. Y. Supp. 189, the judgment appealed from should be reversed, and a new trial ordered, with costs to appellant to abide event. All concur.
